# The `WebAssemblyAsmPrinter.cpp` File Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

This file contains a printer that converts from our internal representation of machine-dependent LLVM code to the <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/webassembly">WebAssembly</a> assembly language. <a href="#details">More...</a>

<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This converts invoke names generated by LowerEmscriptenEHSjLj to real names</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that are expected by JavaScript glue code. The invoke names generated by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Emscripten JS glue code are based on their argument and return types; for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// example, for a function that takes an i32 and returns nothing, it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#39;invoke&#95;vi&#39;. But the format of invoke generated by LowerEmscriptenEHSjLj pass</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// contains a mangled string generated from their IR types, for example,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;&#95;&#95;invoke&#95;void&#95;%struct.mystruct&#42;&#95;int&quot;, because final wasm types are not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// available in the IR pass. So we convert those names to the form that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Emscripten JS code expects.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Refer to LowerEmscriptenEHSjLj pass for more details.</span></CodeLine>
